## Auth / Keycloak

The application is configured as an **OAuth2 Resource Server**.
All secured endpoints require a valid JWT token from the Keycloak realm.

**Realm:** `{{KEYCLOAK_REALM}}`
**Client ID:** `{{KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID}}`

### Request Token (Dev)

```bash
# Get token from Keycloak (password flow – development only!)
curl -X POST http://localhost:8180/realms/{{KEYCLOAK_REALM}}/protocol/openid-connect/token \
  -d "client_id={{KEYCLOAK_CLIENT_ID}}" \
  -d "username=<user>" \
  -d "password=<password>" \
  -d "grant_type=password" | jq '.access_token'
```

